<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="519" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1368,2043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1440,1466]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species can be distinguished from its congeners by the elongate uncus more than three times the length of the saccus and the sinuate ventral margin of the sacculus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="520" pageId="18" pageNumber="519" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1368,2043]" box="[199,819,1512,1539]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1512,1538]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[431,514,1512,1538]" captionStart="FIGURES 10−15" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1349,1373]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,249,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-44@11.[161,1426,237,1326]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 10−15. Adults of Meleonoma spp. 10, M. curvicornuta sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 11, M. dilatilobata sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 12, M. globulosa sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 13, M. prospina sp. nov., paratype, ♀; 14, M. sinuata sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 15, M. unijugata sp. nov., paratype, ♂. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5832804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5832804/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 7.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1368,2043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Head</emphasis>
yellow. Labial palpus pale yellow; first palpomere with scattered black scales; second palpomere with sparse black scales, forming a black ring at apex; third palpomere with several dots on outer and dorsal surfaces. Antenna yellow; scape with scattered black scales on dorsal surface; flagellum annulated with black on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1368,2043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Thorax</emphasis>
yellowish brown, mixed with black; tegula black, yellowish brown apically. Forewing ground color yellow, with greyish-black scales; costal margin with black dot at base and basal 3/5; plical, discal and discocellular dots black, plical dot at distal 1/3 of fold, discal dot at middle of cell, discocellular dots doubled, situated at anterior and posterior angles of cell; terminal dots black, extending from near apex of costal margin along termen to before end of fold; fringe grey, tipped with black around tornus. Hindwing and fringe deep grey. Legs yellow; on ventral surface, femur of foreleg with scattered blackish-brown scales, femur of midleg blackish brown apically, tibiae of fore- and midlegs blackish brown except yellow at middle and at apex respectively, tarsi with blackish-brown scales on each tarsomere, tibia of hindleg with scattered blackish-brown scales, tarsus with sparse blackish-brown scales.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1368,2043]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="520" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis box="[199,365,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[382,468,1980,2007]" captionStart="FIGURES 22−27" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[187,1401,194,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-24@14.[173,1413,181,1843]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 22−27. Male genitalia of Meleonoma spp. 22, M. curvicornuta sp. nov., paratype, slide No. TZL19374; 23, M. dilatilobata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19366; 24, M. globulosa sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19354; 25, M. prospina sp. nov., paratype, slide No. ZXJ19381; 26, M. sinuata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19361; 27, M. unijugata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. ZXJ19362. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5832810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5832810/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Uncus slenderly elongate, slightly wide at base, pointed at apex. Tegumen widened medially, with a large V-shaped anterior emargination; lateral arm narrowed anteriorly, rounded at apex. Valva narrowed near base, then widened to before middle, thereafter slightly narrowed to rounded apex, with a setose pad at base; ventral margin concave inward at basal 1/4, obtusely arched from before middle to apex; costa narrowed to before tip of costal margin, with large sparse setae before middle; transtilla weakly sclerotized, slender, pointed at apex. Sacculus wide basally, distinctly narrowed distally, pointed and directed dorsad apically; dorsal margin semicircularly concave medially; ventral margin sinuate, concave before middle and before apex. Saccus 2/5 length of uncus, subparallelly sided, obtuse on anterior margin. Juxta U-shaped; lateral arm slightly dilated apically. Aedeagus shorter than valva, basal half weakly sclerotized, distal half membranous; cornuti being a narrow row and a large patch of short spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,401,439,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Female unknown.</paragraph>
