<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="520" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,511,537]" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[865,958,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="520">sinuatus</emphasis>
, referring to the sinuate ventral margin of the sacculus.
</paragraph>
